parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded.

sudden shutdown

clutch pedal sticks to the floor

and unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system leaks and overheating can cause engine damage, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: Antifreeze leaks
engine overheating
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system problems can cause loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling
hesitation
and unusual electrical behavior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Emissions system failures can cause environmental harm and affect vehicle performance.
symptoms: Check engine light comes on
difficulty passing emissions tests

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unexpected airbag deployment can cause injuries, accidents, or leave the driver stranded. It can also lead to a loss of control of the vehicle, potentially resulting in a crash.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without warning or impact
while the vehicle is stationary or in motion
sometimes causing injuries or damage to the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy during a crash
even when the vehicle is traveling at a significant speed
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunction of the airbag system can lead to false warnings, unnecessary deployments, or failures to deploy, causing accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbag warning lights illuminate on the dashboard
airbags deploy without warning or impact
or fail to deploy during a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience intermittent electrical issues, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
the vehicle stalls or dies
electrical systems become inoperable
the horn does not work
the battery goes dead suddenly
the vehicle idles high and sputters
the vehicle experiences a short in the electrical system
the wiring harness fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission issues can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or fail to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle revs up to high RPMs
the vehicle jerks and stalls
the vehicle will not get out of first gear
the vehicle experiences stalling problems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or fail to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience intermittent engine issues, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Smoke comes from under the hood
the engine revs up to high RPMs
the engine stalls or dies
the spark plug is shot out of the engine.
